
This project is a Gas Leakage Detection System developed using an Arduino Uno and MQ135 gas sensor. The system continuously monitors the surrounding air for harmful gases and pollutants. When the gas concentration exceeds a predefined threshold value, the Arduino activates a buzzer and LED to provide both audible and visual alerts.

The project is designed to enhance safety in homes, laboratories, industries, and other environments where harmful gases may be present. It is a low-cost, easy-to-implement solution for real-time gas monitoring and early warning.

Components Used

- Arduino Uno
- MQ135 Gas Sensor
- Active Buzzer
- LED
- Breadboard
- Jumper Wires

Features

- Real-time gas detection
- Audible alarm using buzzer
- Visual indication using LED
- Serial Monitor output for monitoring gas values
- Simple and low-cost implementation

Working Principle

The MQ135 sensor detects harmful gases and sends an analog signal to the Arduino. The Arduino continuously reads the sensor value and compares it with a predefined threshold. If the gas concentration exceeds the threshold, the buzzer and LED are activated to alert users. Otherwise, the system remains in monitoring mode.

